message.content: "cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR". The paper deals with the intersection of computer vision and natural language processing, specifically in the context of visual question answering. Therefore, "cs.CV" (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) and "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) are also relevant due to the use of machine learning techniques in the proposed approach. Finally, "cs.IR" (Information Retrieval) is a possible sub-category due to the focus on information extraction from visual content.
